                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d929">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">437.11H23/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Williamson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-16T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 16, 1926—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. Department’s instruction 720, June 12, 1926. Foreign Office reply in Harrah
                    case received yesterday. Text and translation go forward in tomorrow’s
                        pouch.<note n="16" xml:id="d929fn16">Foreign Office note of July 13, 1926,
                        not printed.</note> In 18–page note Government courteously but categorically
                    refuses to entertain proposal of arbitration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williamson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
